===Etymology 1===
The sense of "safeguard" comes from {{etyl|la}} {{term|Palladium|lang=la}} (the image of {{term|Pallas}} that protected {{term|Troy}}), from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Παλλάδιον|lang=grc}}, from {{term|Παλλάς|lang=grc}}, an alternative name for {{term|Athena}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|pl=palladia}}

# A safeguard {{qualifier|from a statue of Athena that was believed to safeguard the ancient city of Troy}}.

